Job Description
Cyber & Information Security Consultant
Warwickshire
Inside IR35

My client is looking to recruit Cyber & Information Security Consultant for their operations across Warwickshire.
You will help by bringing advanced knowledge of Cyber Security and working alongside the wider ICT team.
As a Senior Cyber Security Engineer, you will be responsible for Operational Excellence focussing on the design and implementation of best practices and solutions to defend against hackers, cyber-attacks and other persistent threats.
3 to 5 years experience of Cyber Security experience is a must, within the public sector being the most desirable.

Key responsibilities will include:

Providing expertise and advise on good practice Cyber & Security policies and standards in line with relevant regulation (NCSC);
Providing technical support provided to the Cyber Security team;
Advising and taking part in knowledge transfer and training sessions to the wider ICT team;
Participating in multi-discipline projects acting as the Cyber Security Subject Matter Expert in scoping, researching, vendor selection; implementation, configuration, documentation and roll out of strategic infrastructure technologies;
Demonstrating improvement in response to incidents.
If interested and have the sklills and experience required, please apply immediately Job Description
